{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ketan/project/dropkick","sessionId":"3f1208fc-21f7-4873-bdce-4d7617029ebb","version":"2.1.72","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a45bac773491662a2","slug":"sleepy-munching-marble","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are implementing Ansible roles and scripts for a CI system called \"Dropkick CI\" in /home/ketan/project/dropkick/. Write ALL files completely — no placeholders.\n\n## Role: msmtp (`ansible/roles/msmtp/`)\n\n### `tasks/main.yml`\n1. Install msmtp, msmtp-mta packages\n2. Deploy `/etc/msmtprc` from template (mode 0600, owner root)\n\n### `templates/msmtprc.j2`\n```\ndefaults\nauth           on\ntls            on\ntls_starttls   on\nlogfile        /var/log/msmtp.log\n\naccount        default\nhost           {{ vault_smtp_host }}\nport           587\nfrom           {{ notify_email_from }}\nuser           {{ vault_smtp_user }}\npassword       {{ vault_smtp_password }}\n```\n\n## Core Scripts\n\n### `ansible/roles/ci-poller/files/poll.sh`\n~80 lines, bash script with `set -euo pipefail`. Logic:\n- `flock -n /var/run/dropkick/poll.lock` (wrap entire script body in flock block, exit 0 if can't acquire)\n- `REPOS_CONFIG=/etc/dropkick/repos.yaml`\n- `STATE_DIR=/var/lib/dropkick/state`\n- `LOG=/var/log/dropkick/poll.log`\n- Log function that prefixes timestamp\n- Parse repos from config using `yq '.repos[]' -o json \"$REPOS_CONFIG\"` then iterate\n- For each repo (use yq to extract name, url, branch, from json):\n  - `git ls-remote \"$url\" \"refs/heads/$branch\"` to get current hash (extract first field)\n  - Compare to `$STATE_DIR/$name/last-commit` (read file if exists, else empty)\n  - If different:\n    - Log \"Change detected for $name: $old_hash -> $new_hash\"\n    - Run `laminarc run \"$name\"` (capture exit code, don't fail script)\n    - Write new hash to state file REGARDLESS of job result (prevents infinite retrigger)\n    - Log result\n  - Else: log \"No changes for $name\"\n- Use `exec 200>/var/run/dropkick/poll.lock` and `flock -n 200 || { log \"Another poll is running\"; exit 0; }` pattern\n\n### `ansible/roles/ci-poller/files/notify.sh`\n~20 lines, bash script with `set -euo pipefail`:\n- Parse args: `--job`, `--run`, `--result`, `--to`\n- Compose email with subject `[Dropkick CI] $JOB #$RUN: $RESULT`\n- Body includes job name, run number, result, and link to `http://localhost:8080/jobs/$JOB/$RUN`\n- Send via: `msmtp -t` with heredoc containing To, From, Subject, body\n\n## Role: ci-poller (`ansible/roles/ci-poller/`)\n\n### `tasks/main.yml`\n1. Deploy repos.yaml to `/etc/dropkick/repos.yaml` (copy from `{{ playbook_dir }}/../config/repos.yaml`)\n2. Deploy poll.sh to `/usr/local/bin/dropkick-poll` (mode 0755)\n3. Deploy notify.sh to `/usr/local/bin/dropkick-notify` (mode 0755)\n4. Generate Laminar job.run scripts for each repo (loop over `repos` variable):\n   - Template `job.run.j2` to `/var/lib/laminar/cfg/jobs/{{ item.name }}.run` (mode 0755)\n5. Generate Laminar job.after scripts for each repo:\n   - Template `job.after.j2` to `/var/lib/laminar/cfg/jobs/{{ item.name }}.after` (mode 0755)\n6. Find existing job scripts in `/var/lib/laminar/cfg/jobs/`\n7. Remove orphaned job scripts (those not matching any repo in config)\n8. Create state directories for each repo: `/var/lib/dropkick/state/{{ item.name }}`\n9. Deploy systemd service from template `dropkick-poll.service.j2`\n10. Deploy systemd timer from template `dropkick-poll.timer.j2`\n11. Enable and start the timer, notify handler\n12. Deploy logrotate config from template\n\n### `handlers/main.yml`\n- Handler \"reload systemd\": systemd daemon-reload\n- Handler \"restart dropkick-poll timer\": restart dropkick-poll.timer\n\n### `templates/job.run.j2`\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nWORKSPACE=\"/var/lib/laminar/run/{{ item.name }}/workspace\"\n\n# Ensure workspace exists\nif [ ! -d \"$WORKSPACE/.git\" ]; then\n    git clone \"{{ item.url }}\" \"$WORKSPACE\"\nfi\n\ncd \"$WORKSPACE\"\ngit fetch origin\ngit checkout \"origin/{{ item.branch }}\" --force\ngit clean -fdx\n\n# Run the build command\n{% if item.timeout is defined %}\ntimeout {{ item.timeout }} {{ item.command }}\n{% else %}\n{{ item.command }}\n{% endif %}\n```\n\n### `templates/job.after.j2`\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nif [ \"$RESULT\" != \"success\" ]; then\n    NOTIFY_EMAIL=\"{{ item.notify_email | default(notify_email_to) }}\"\n    /usr/local/bin/dropkick-notify \\\n        --job \"$JOB\" \\\n        --run \"$RUN\" \\\n        --result \"$RESULT\" \\\n        --to \"$NOTIFY_EMAIL\"\nfi\n```\n\n### `templates/dropkick-poll.service.j2`\n```ini\n[Unit]\nDescription=Dropkick CI poller\nAfter=network-online.target\nWants=network-online.target\n\n[Service]\nType=oneshot\nUser={{ dropkick_user }}\nExecStart=/usr/local/bin/dropkick-poll\n```\n\n### `templates/dropkick-poll.timer.j2`\n```ini\n[Unit]\nDescription=Dropkick CI polling timer\n\n[Timer]\nOnBootSec=1min\nOnUnitActiveSec={{ poll_interval_minutes }}min\nAccuracySec=30s\n\n[Install]\nWantedBy=timers.target\n```\n\n### `templates/logrotate-dropkick.j2`\n```\n/var/log/dropkick/*.log {\n    daily\n    rotate 14\n    compress\n    delaycompress\n    missingok\n    notifempty\n    create 0644 {{ dropkick_user }} {{ dropkick_user }}\n}\n```\n\nCreate all necessary directories and files now.\n"},"uuid":"994b36ee-5321-4540-ad68-13b732f45b31","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:12:21.091Z"}
